# Project Overview

RustyGate is a lightweight Rust LLM inference gateway portfolio project. It demonstrates async Rust web services, provider abstraction, routing, fallback, streaming responses, observability, token/cost estimates, and clean tests.

- Keep the project small, polished, and documentation-first.
- Avoid heavy infrastructure unless the user explicitly requests it.
- Prefer simple, testable implementations over broad abstractions.
- Preserve a simplified OpenAI-compatible shape where practical.
- Favor readable, documented Rust over clever Rust.
- Ask before adding major dependencies or framework layers.
- Keep secrets out of logs, examples, docs, and commits.
- The MVP and post-MVP hardening are complete. Keep future work focused on validation, bugs, docs, and small hardening unless a new roadmap is explicitly opened.
- Do not add Kubernetes, Redis, dashboards, multi-user billing, semantic caching, production policy engines, or full OpenAI compatibility without explicit approval.
